CSS :
1. inline : style inside element (element specfic)
      style attribute 

2. internal : style inside document : style tag
<style>   CSS </style>

3. external  : File.CSS
    application specific 
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="Styele.css"/>

Loading Process 
 Style loading process is based on the stack order.
  internal  --- >  external   (external) 
  external  -----> internal  (internal)
  internal  --- >  external ---> inline   (inline -->external-->internal) 
  external  -----> internal --> inline    (inline--> internal--> external)

 color : color is a style property 
             color is a font color 
             color is a text color 

             color="value"
 How we can specify colors :

    1.  color : name  (red,green,blue,orange)

    2.  color : rgb()   (red,green,blue)  (0-255,0-255,0-255)
       rgb(0,0,0)  rgb(255,255,255)  rgb(0,0,255)  rgb(0,255,0)
         rgb(255,0,0) 
   
   3. Hash value :    combination of charecters and numbers 
        #000 #FFF   #234fdc 


 background-color :  background-color is a style property 
             backgroundcolor is a background color  of element

             1. name
             2. rgb
             3. hash  

class specifier :  

   class is the important specifier for html loading in css .
    in Styles classes are recogniging using a dot symbol.
    in html element  class is a special attribute.






